$ Avaloq script packages

{ chart

  Create charts and graphs
 (→ Companies-Products/Avaloq/development/report-writer[report writer]).

}
{ util

  Special characters (→ development/line-break[new line], tabulator …), numbers (pi …), dates.

}
{ format

  `format` is used to format numbers etc.

}
{ err

  `err` is used for a consistent formatting of error messages.


code {
…
exception when others then
  err.raise_fa(
    'some string',
    'variable_one', variable_one,
    'variable_two', variable_two
     …
  );
code }

}
{ msg_lib #avq-msg_lib

  Used in conjunction with → Companies-Products/Avaloq/AMI.

}
{ netw_release #avq-netw_release

  Used in conjunction with → Companies-Products/Avaloq/AMI.

}
{ session

code {
session.debug('…');
code }

code {
session.raise_ui_err(1, 'Some error message here');
code }

}
{ tab

  Text based tables.

  The package is deprecated in favour of `mem_tab`.

}
{ text_list

  To process lists of text.

}
{ PL/SQL packages

  In an Avaloq script package of → Companies-Products/Avaloq/development/sources[source] type PGK
  (Avaloq script package), a → development/databases/Oracle/PL-SQL[PL/SQL] package can be imported with `import native`.

  Unfortunately, Avaloq wants to eliminate this usefule feature.

}
sa:
  → Companies-Products/Avaloq/development/Avaloq-script[Avaloq script].
